{
  "texts": [
    "Estimates for magic-state yieldLet us attempt to model the error rate of the components of the device using the yield we have evaluated experimentally.",
    "The yield is a helpful figure of merit as it tells us precisely how often a single-error event occurs to leading order in the error rate.",
    "We first try to model the yield using simple three-parameter models that we derive below.",
    "We also compare the yield to numerical simulations of our circuits.",
    "We show the estimated yield for different experiments in Extended Data Table 3, in comparison with our analytical model and numerical results.Both of our analyses have good agreement with the experiment if we assume a two-qubit gate-error rate and a measurement error rate of the order of 2%."
  ]
}